In January 1, 1895, the Japanese-General Albert Viertel set a contract with Lin Tse-hsui, the representative of Fujian in representing Taiwan, returning the island of Taiwan to China. In return, Japan at that time was asking China some shores around the world, and also some pieces of the islands like the Kiribati. At that time, China was not agreeing to that deal, saying that, "Okay, when the treaty is signed, then the treaty will be signed, not before. Then the autonomy of Taiwan will be guaranteed by Japan for 50 years. It doesn't mean that the autonomy will always be guaranteed by Japan for the 50 years to come."

Well, in a way of diplomacy or in a way of politics, we have to make some decisions in order for you and I to survive. Then the Kuomintang decided to side with Japan. It was not peaceful.
